  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He hath filled me with bitterness,.... Or \"with bitternesses\" (m); instead of food, bitter herbs; the allusion perhaps is to the bitter herbs eaten at the passover, and signify bitter afflictions, sore calamities, of which the prophet and his people had their fill. The Targum is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"with the gall of serpents;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "see Job 20:14; ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Job 20:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he hath made me drunken with wormwood; with wormwood drink; but this herb being a wholesome one, though bitter, some think that henbane, or wolfsbane, is rather meant, which is of a poisonous and intoxicating nature; it is no unusual thing for persons to be represented as drunk with affliction, Isaiah 51:17. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "he hath made me drunken with wormwood; with wormwood drink; but this herb being a wholesome one, though bitter, some think that henbane, or wolfsbane, is rather meant, which is of a poisonous and intoxicating nature; it is no unusual thing for persons to be represented as drunk with affliction, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 51:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
